<section class="sec" id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-h">
  <div class="lc">
    <div class="faq-inner">
      <div class="faq-header">
        <span class="eyebrow rv">Common Questions</span>
        <h2 id="faq-h" class="h2 rv" style="transition-delay:0.08s">
          Questions worth asking.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">

        <details class="faq-item rv" style="transition-delay:0.06s">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            How is this different from hiring a PR agency?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">
            PR gets you mentioned. We get you chosen. A PR agency places stories; we build the strategic
            position that makes those stories — and every other touchpoint — convert into business.
            Media is one tool. It's never the strategy.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item rv" style="transition-delay:0.1s">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            How long before I see results?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">
            The honest answer: it depends on where you're starting. Some clients see inbound shift within
            8–12 weeks. Market repositioning at scale takes 6–12 months. We'll tell you what's realistic
            in the strategy call, not what you want to hear.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item rv" style="transition-delay:0.14s">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            Do you manage my social media?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">
            We can. But that's not the point. We build the strategy and messaging architecture that makes
            your content work. Whether we execute it, your team does, or we do it together depends on what
            makes sense for your business.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item rv" style="transition-delay:0.18s">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            What does it cost?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">
            We work on retained engagements tailored to scope. This isn't a productised service, because
            your positioning shouldn't be either. Book a strategy call — we'll scope it properly and give
            you a clear number.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item rv" style="transition-delay:0.22s">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            I'm already well-known in my industry. Do I need this?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">
            Known and positioned aren't the same thing. If your reputation doesn't generate inbound revenue
            from outside your existing network, it's a ceiling — not a platform. We turn local authority
            into market position.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item rv" style="transition-delay:0.26s">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            I've been burned by agencies before. Why would this be different?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">
            Probably because the last one sold you activity, not outcomes. Content calendars, post schedules,
            follower counts — none of which answered the only question that matters: did it generate revenue?
            We start with that question. Everything we build is measured against it.
          </p>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
